[[lt:Pasaulio šalių didmiesčiai]]

'''Reference datum height''' ('''RDH''') is the height of a point that is located above the intersection of the runway centre line and the [[runway|threshold]] and through which the downward extended straight portion of the [[glide path]] passes.<ref>[http://www.eurocontrol.int/lexicon/lexicon/en/index.php/Instrument_Landing_System_Reference_Datum_Height Instrument Landing System Reference Datum Height] Eurocontrol.int</ref> It is usually found on the aerodrome [[instrument approach]] charts.

